enhanced_by.reason: Both methods modify the state of the stack by adding or removing elements.
Both methods interact with the top element of the stack, though pop removes it while peek does not.
Both methods return the top element of the stack, making peek a good candidate for constructing assertions about the state of the stack before and after pop.
The search method can be used to verify the absence of the popped element, ensuring that pop correctly removes the element from the stack.
